    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>How to: Start an Application</Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph>To write a standard Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF) application in procedural code, you must implement it as a class that inherits from Application. You then create a stub class to serve as an entry point. This class typically only contains the application's <Run FontWeight="Bold">Main</Run>
 method. It creates an instance of your class, and calls Run to launch the application. This example shows how to launch a WPF application from <Run FontWeight="Bold">Main</Run>
.
    </Paragraph>

    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>Note: 
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>Extensible Application Markup Language (XAML)-based applications do not need to explicitly create an entry point or call Run to launch the application. This is handled automatically by the build process when it parses the <Hyperlink NavigateUri="32b1c054-5aca-423b-b4b5-ed8dc4dc637d.xaml">Application Management Overview</Hyperlink>
.
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22">Example
    </Paragraph>

    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>C++ </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph xml:space="preserve" TextAlignment="Left" FontSize="8pt" FontFamily="Courier New"><Run>SimpleProcedural::app^ app = gcnew SimpleProcedural::app(); 
app->Run(); 
</Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>C# </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph xml:space="preserve" TextAlignment="Left" FontSize="8pt" FontFamily="Courier New"><Run>app app = new app(); 
app.Run(); 
</Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

